text: Clinch County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. It was created on February 14, 1850. It was named in honor of Duncan Lamont Clinch. As of the 2020 census, the population was 6,749. The county seat is Homerville. ==References== Category:1850s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1850 establishments in the United States Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
